The paper proposes a new architecture for crowd counting using convolutional neural networks (CNNs) and focuses on computer vision tasks. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also introduces a new loss function to improve network generalization, which falls under the category of machine learning and artificial intelligence, cs.AI. The use of CNNs for crowd counting is a popular research area, and the paper proposes a new architecture that improves the state-of-the-art, which is relevant to the sub-category of machine learning, cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also conducts experiments on several datasets, including video data, which falls under the sub-category of multimedia, cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the paper proposes a method for crowd counting that can be applied to robotics applications, which is relevant to the sub-category of robotics, cs.RO (Robotics).
